-- Indian December Coal Imports for Power Rise 31%, India Coal Says
-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 2012-01-19T06:58:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/indian-december-coal-imports-for-power-rise-31-india-coal-says.html
Indian power utilities increased
coal imports in December by 31 percent from a year earlier to
3.37 million metric tons, India Coal Market Watch said, citing
the  Central Electricity Authority .  Total supplies received by power plants, both domestic and
imports, rose 13 percent last month to 38.26 million tons from a
year ago, according to the newsletter published by Kolkata-based
online trading company Mjunction Services Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in New Delhi at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
